Rating: 3
Very good, ideal for a stylish summer lunch. Agreed it was a bit time-consuming to make, but dill sauce can be made ahead, and would go nicely with grilled or smoked salmon, or similar fish, as well. I substituted grilled peppers and chopped walnuts for the celery and green olives as didn't have on hand/husband olive hater, as well as juice of one lime to substitute for some of the lemon juice. Next day, I added some chopped black olives and stuffed inside pita bread with some salad leaves....makes a great sandwich.

